<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7531&amp;p=74870#p74870"><![CDATA[
I was programming an Apple IIe in assembly language back in middle school in the early 1990s, which is how I learned 6502 asm. I became interested in NES emulation sometime in the 2000s, and I wrote a few demos that worked on the emulators of the time but not necessarily on NES hardware because I had no way to test. Zophar.net had some of the documents (including koitsu's that you mention). I coded for the NES off and on, mixed with PC and GBA coding. My interest in NES programming really picked up once I got my PowerPak and could see my work run on the real thing.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Tue Mar 01, 2011 6:11 am</p><hr />
